vectorData.altText: 19. What movement is occurring in the knuckles?
That's right!  The fingers are moving away from the midline of the hand, which is the middle finger. This is abductioB.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, and then come back to try again.

Perform these movements as illustrated. 
In the case of the fingers, the “midline” is not the midline of the body, but the midline of the hand, running through the middle finger.
